Reference-contexts: Annalysis of collected data. Twelve CS students with little pen experience were chosen as subjects. Four diagrams of similar complexity were selected, one each from the categories of dataflow visual programs, Petri nets, flowcharts, and state diagrams. We have developed a pen-based diagram editor for GO's PenPoint <ref> [1] </ref> running on NCR3125 pen computer [9]. The editor can recognize and respond to shapes and gesture commands. Appsoft's Draw version 1.02 [4] on NeXT was used as the mouse-based diagram editor. A random task assignment table was constructed. Procedures and instruction sheets for the subjects were prepared.
