Reference-contexts: The existing tools for diagram drawing, such as MacDraw, use the mouse/menu paradigm of user interface. The pen/gesture paradigm offers a possibly improved alternative. The pen user interface is heralded as more natural and powerful than the mouse, due to pointing, handwriting, gesturing, and drawing <ref> [3, 5, 6] </ref>. It is widely believed that the pen is mightier than the mouse. There are comparison studies of different input devices such as pen, mouse and keyboard in different application areas, e.g., [10] for spreadsheet applications and [8] for text entry.
